      <head>Bernhard Seidmann</head>

      <div>
        <p>Swiss conductor, founder-director in 1943 of the Zurich Motet Choir.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <head>Seidmann and Schenker</head>

        <p>Two items of correspondence are known to survive from Seidmann to Schenker, OC 44/49 and
          50, July 8 and August 29, 1934, inquiring about Schenker's edition of the complete
          Beethoven sonatas and indicating that he has long owned the <title level="m">Erl√§uterungsausgabe</title>;  at the time, Seidmann was living in
          Dresden.  Schenker's response to the first letter is not known to survive. </p>

      </div>
